  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6602.96 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6607 and massive positive gamma wall at 6605 (+11.7B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push higher into that level while providing strong support on dips toward 6600 (+9.6B). The PIN regime with 39.5B total GEX creates a powerful mean-reversion setup, with dealers acting as stabilizers around current levels - the recent wall break and GEX surge events suggest we just saw significant options flow that's now pinning price action. Key resistance at 6605-6610 should cap upside moves, while 6600 and ultimately 6500 (-4.5B negative gamma) mark critical support levels where dealer buying intensifies.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get stuck between 6600-6610 with dealers fighting moves in either direction.",
